1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:02,265
(Previously)
I can't believe you're still trying.

2
00:00:02,289 --> 00:00:04,280
I said I need time to heal.

3
00:00:04,313 --> 00:00:05,520
You focus on moving on.

4
00:00:05,556 --> 00:00:07,076
I'll focus on scoring points with you.

5
00:00:07,610 --> 00:00:08,036
Oh!

6
00:00:08,061 --> 00:00:09,378
I brought Veha out.

7
00:00:09,403 --> 00:00:10,403
I came with Kanit.

8
00:00:11,230 --> 00:00:12,953
But Kanit should've really bumped into me,

9
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:14,443
so he'd forgive me.

10
00:00:14,770 --> 00:00:16,024
I'll stand by your side.

11
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:17,680
Stay away from him.

12
00:00:18,230 --> 00:00:19,230
You're ruining his image.

13
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:20,523
F**k you!

14
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,215
Are you really getting with him?

15
00:00:22,350 --> 00:00:23,969
Why can't I be with him?

16
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,101
I'm single now.

17
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:26,947
Can you sleep with me tonight?

18
00:00:27,610 --> 00:00:28,751
You mean sleeping next to each other?

19
00:00:28,775 --> 00:00:29,981
I mean having sex.

20
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:02,410
What time is it now?

21
00:01:04,260 --> 00:01:05,366
It's already 8:30.

22
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:08,360
This is so nice.

23
00:01:09,250 --> 00:01:10,406
I slept like a log.

24
00:01:12,940 --> 00:01:15,460
I've never had a chance
to sleep on a soft bed like this before.

25
00:01:16,390 --> 00:01:17,390
You know what?

26
00:01:17,930 --> 00:01:19,686
I once ordered a mattress online.

27
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:22,000
I wanted the kind they
use in five-star hotels.

28
00:01:22,264 --> 00:01:24,110
But damn, when it was delivered,

29
00:01:24,141 --> 00:01:25,981
it felt more like something
from a love motel.

30
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,544
It was hard as hell.

31
00:01:34,810 --> 00:01:35,810
Are you okay?

32
00:01:38,190 --> 00:01:39,569
I need to hurry to work.

33
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,600
Are you leaving now?

34
00:01:43,230 --> 00:01:44,393
I have to go to work too.

35
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:46,400
Okay, I'm going to take a shower.

36
00:01:46,610 --> 00:01:48,090
You can take care of yourself, right?

37
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:01,860
Want some coffee?

38
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:02,849
It's alright.

39
00:02:03,175 --> 00:02:04,738
I prefer street coffee.

40
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:06,640
Diabetes in a cup.

41
00:02:10,553 --> 00:02:11,793
Do you want me to drop you off?

42
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:15,236
It's alright. I should go by myself.

43
00:02:16,260 --> 00:02:18,892
Besides, I think your job is done now.

44
00:02:19,530 --> 00:02:22,289
Hey, there's still a lot
of quota left. Just use it.

45
00:02:22,990 --> 00:02:23,433
Let's go.

46
00:02:23,778 --> 00:02:25,138
I used it up last night.

47
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:35,680
Here.

48
00:02:37,270 --> 00:02:38,270
What's this?

49
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:39,920
A debt release agreement.

50
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:42,800
Like I told you last night,

51
00:02:43,390 --> 00:02:44,855
I'm forgiving all your debt.

52
00:02:45,950 --> 00:02:47,175
I thought you were joking.

53
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:48,855
I wasn't expecting anything.

54
00:02:49,569 --> 00:02:51,689
I wasn't going to use you
to vent my sadness for free.

55
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:04,070
So this is what it feels
like to be a whore.

56
00:03:05,083 --> 00:03:07,080
Don't think like that.

57
00:03:07,390 --> 00:03:08,953
Last night, you helped me.

58
00:03:09,330 --> 00:03:11,033
Lately, you've been taking me around.

59
00:03:11,570 --> 00:03:13,261
And you even punched Lion.

60
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:16,923
I counted that as a bonus,
and it all added up to clear your debt.

61
00:03:20,812 --> 00:03:22,393
From now on,

62
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:24,940
you don't have to take care of me anymore.

63
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,350
What if I just want to take care of you?

64
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:43,360
I can take care of myself.

65
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:12,412
DEBTOR'S SIGNATURE

66
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:24,960
I'm leaving then.

67
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:34,898
If you need help, call me anytime.

68
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,700
"A Dog and A Plane" (Episode 6)

69
00:06:06,890 --> 00:06:07,890
Damn!

70
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,769
You slept with him and dumped him.

71
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,406
You basically tricked him into sex.

72
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:14,270
That's really harsh.

73
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,030
Tricked him into sex?

74
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:18,332
It was more like comfort sex,

75
00:06:18,369 --> 00:06:22,067
a way to vent feelings and feel better.

76
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:24,301
If you wanted to feel better,

77
00:06:24,332 --> 00:06:26,300
you could've just called me and vented.

78
00:06:26,332 --> 00:06:29,138
You took your feelings out on him.

79
00:06:29,169 --> 00:06:30,418
What if he caught feelings?

80
00:06:30,436 --> 00:06:31,378
What are you going to do?

81
00:06:31,384 --> 00:06:33,187
Please. He won't.

82
00:06:33,753 --> 00:06:35,987
He's probably been through
this kind of thing a lot.

83
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,412
What about you?

84
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,000
Weren't you catching feelings?

85
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,858
You're a romantic.

86
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:46,818
Love is your religion. I know you, Kanit.

87
00:06:46,861 --> 00:06:49,969
If you didn't feel anything,
you wouldn't have done it.

88
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:55,430
Oh.

89
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,184
Silence.

90
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,356
Silence. The conversation got cut off.

91
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,255
You caught feelings,

92
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,440
but you're pretending to deny your heart

93
00:07:01,495 --> 00:07:03,187
like a K-drama female lead.

94
00:07:03,236 --> 00:07:04,972
Your words don't match your heart.

95
00:07:05,330 --> 00:07:07,987
Come on. I didn't feel anything.

96
00:07:08,012 --> 00:07:10,461
Look, I'm the new Kanit.

97
00:07:10,498 --> 00:07:11,507
From now on,

98
00:07:11,538 --> 00:07:13,889
I won't give my heart to anyone again.

99
00:07:13,907 --> 00:07:15,076
Yeah!

100
00:07:15,370 --> 00:07:16,947
Classic.

101
00:07:16,972 --> 00:07:19,280
Pushing love away,
only to realize your feelings.

102
00:07:19,323 --> 00:07:21,501
Before you know it, you're in episode 15.

103
00:07:26,370 --> 00:07:30,166
Oppa, I'm sorry.

104
00:07:30,190 --> 00:07:31,784
It's my fault.

105
00:07:31,809 --> 00:07:33,987
I just realized my feelings.

106
00:07:34,018 --> 00:07:35,980
I'm in love with you.

107
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,892
Saranghaeyo.

108
00:07:39,740 --> 00:07:40,406
Pailin.

109
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:41,590
Hmm?

110
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:43,298
You watch too many series.

111
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:45,286
Go check on the passengers.

112
00:07:45,329 --> 00:07:46,541
Fine.

113
00:07:46,790 --> 00:07:47,938
Remember my words.

114
00:07:47,969 --> 00:07:48,969
Remember them.

115
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,206
ZOR ZO'S MEAT SALAD,
SPICY &amp; TUMMY-FILLING

116
00:08:05,938 --> 00:08:06,938
Mmm…

117
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,560
Damn.

118
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:11,446
What's this? It's so good.

119
00:08:11,489 --> 00:08:12,941
Fried foot skin, maybe.

120
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:16,203
It's obviously lime. Why'd you even ask?

121
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:18,732
Hey, I want this to go.

122
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,276
The foot skin or the lime?

123
00:08:20,289 --> 00:08:20,892
The lime.

124
00:08:20,916 --> 00:08:21,916
Okay.

125
00:08:22,123 --> 00:08:24,120
Can I also get the fried meat salad to go?

126
00:08:24,153 --> 00:08:25,741
You've been ordering
a lot of takeout lately.

127
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,578
What's going on?

128
00:08:26,603 --> 00:08:27,907
Why don't you just eat here?

129
00:08:30,150 --> 00:08:31,446
I'm taking it to my junior.

130
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:33,132
Oh.

131
00:08:37,003 --> 00:08:38,003
Junior?

132
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:39,470
You call him a junior now?

133
00:08:39,495 --> 00:08:40,787
You used to call him a bitch.

134
00:08:40,806 --> 00:08:42,258
He's a junior at my school.

135
00:08:42,295 --> 00:08:43,735
What else am I supposed to call him?

136
00:08:43,930 --> 00:08:44,930
F*cker!

137
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,080
I should call him a f*cker?

138
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:49,236
He acts like I don't have feelings.

139
00:08:49,930 --> 00:08:52,258
He slept with me for one night
and said he was just lonely.

140
00:08:52,530 --> 00:08:53,530
That's it?

141
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:55,286
Come on, bro.

142
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:57,993
People do FWB all the time these days.

143
00:08:58,941 --> 00:09:01,286
In your case, it's a one-night stand.

144
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:03,316
Just one night and that's it.

145
00:09:05,309 --> 00:09:08,189
For me, it's “Sleep with me,
free minced pork salad.”

146
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:12,560
How can he just sleep with me
and dump me like this?

147
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,680
Huh?

148
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:22,393
Once I love someone, I never leave them.

149
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:25,864
I've been genuine.

150
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:28,584
I'm serious, not flirting for fun.

151
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:31,790
He even freaking threw money at me.

152
00:09:31,970 --> 00:09:34,664
This meal is on me. I'm rich.

153
00:09:38,420 --> 00:09:39,420
Where are you going, To?

154
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:41,650
Hey.

155
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:42,732
I'm telling you,

156
00:09:42,775 --> 00:09:44,295
this bastard is tricking you into sex.

157
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:46,356
He doesn't love you for real.

158
00:09:46,381 --> 00:09:47,545
True love doesn't exist in this world.

159
00:09:47,569 --> 00:09:49,107
What the hell?

160
00:09:49,138 --> 00:09:50,621
Hey, To! What's wrong with you?

161
00:09:50,670 --> 00:09:51,741
I'm sorry.

162
00:09:51,772 --> 00:09:52,772
My bro is drunk.

163
00:09:52,940 --> 00:09:53,673
What's wrong?

164
00:09:53,710 --> 00:09:54,720
You're drunk.

165
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,216
Why are you taking it out on other people?

166
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,870
No one really loves you in this world.

167
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:00,276
The only true love is self-love.

168
00:10:00,307 --> 00:10:01,307
You want a fight?

169
00:10:03,650 --> 00:10:04,147
Easy!

170
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:04,615
Easy!

171
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:06,006
Let him go.

172
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:08,184
I'm sorry. Please don't fight.

173
00:10:08,210 --> 00:10:09,292
Today, it's on the house.

174
00:10:09,323 --> 00:10:10,326
Let's just move on.

175
00:10:10,498 --> 00:10:11,390
That's enough.

176
00:10:11,427 --> 00:10:12,664
Let's go eat somewhere else.

177
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:13,649
This place is full of rowdy people.

178
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:14,667
Let's go.

179
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,889
Yeah! Just go!

180
00:10:17,907 --> 00:10:19,427
Go love each other somewhere far away!

181
00:10:19,810 --> 00:10:20,810
Shut up!

182
00:10:22,381 --> 00:10:23,969
Don't you feel pathetic?

183
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:27,729
He said he didn't want anyone
to take care of him.

184
00:10:27,753 --> 00:10:29,815
Why are you sitting here moping,

185
00:10:29,850 --> 00:10:31,452
getting wasted, and lashing out at people?

186
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,505
Does that even make sense?

187
00:10:32,529 --> 00:10:33,740
You need to fight.

188
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,870
Fight for what?

189
00:10:35,901 --> 00:10:37,267
He doesn't want me!

190
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:38,304
What kind of man are you?

191
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:40,760
Why are you giving up so easily?

192
00:10:41,210 --> 00:10:42,770
Bird Thongchai taught us in his lyrics.

193
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,440
Have you listened to his songs?

194
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:50,800
“Gucci, Prada, I've got them for you too.”

195
00:10:50,843 --> 00:10:52,597
Alright, he did say that,
but that's not relevant.

196
00:10:52,621 --> 00:10:54,012
What he actually said was,

197
00:10:54,055 --> 00:10:56,849
“Don't let any problems beat you.”

198
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:58,310
That's right.

199
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,640
What's that tattoo under your breast say?

200
00:11:01,130 --> 00:11:02,490
Here!
ONLY THE DETERMINED WILL WIN.

201
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,741
Only the determined will win.

202
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,170
Yeah!

203
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:11,255
This is what Sek Loso
taught you in his song.

204
00:11:11,273 --> 00:11:13,250
Aren't you going to follow what he taught?

205
00:11:14,220 --> 00:11:15,236
Right.

206
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,243
Aren't you going to listen to Sek?

207
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:20,070
If you love him, go tell him.

208
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,880
If you get hurt, then fight for it.

209
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,550
Dogs like us

210
00:11:23,590 --> 00:11:25,821
have to bark all the way up to the plane.

211
00:11:25,864 --> 00:11:26,864
Go!

212
00:11:26,890 --> 00:11:28,130
Are you going to fight or what?

213
00:11:29,370 --> 00:11:30,584
I'll fight!

214
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:34,652
Woo!

215
00:11:39,630 --> 00:11:40,941
So, are we going out tonight?

216
00:11:40,978 --> 00:11:41,716
I want to go out.

217
00:11:41,735 --> 00:11:45,378
I'm going to get drunk
and forget everything.

218
00:11:45,409 --> 00:11:48,295
Look, alcohol isn't going to help.

219
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:49,243
What should we do?

220
00:11:49,286 --> 00:11:51,483
How about you find someone new?

221
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,772
I need a break.

222
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,256
If I were to get with someone,

223
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:57,250
it'd just be casual.

224
00:11:57,304 --> 00:11:59,895
Anything serious will take time.

225
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:03,350
It won't be hard to find.

226
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:05,501
There he is. Look.

227
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,901
Welcome to the ground,

228
00:12:13,938 --> 00:12:15,076
Mr. Flight Attendant Kanit.

229
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,200
Hey.

230
00:12:18,430 --> 00:12:19,476
What are you doing here?

231
00:12:19,495 --> 00:12:21,224
Why did you bring a garland?

232
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:23,981
I came to see you and tell you this.

233
00:12:26,290 --> 00:12:27,316
I like you.

234
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:29,187
I freaking like you.

235
00:12:36,140 --> 00:12:37,630
What are you, an idol?

236
00:12:37,655 --> 00:12:40,055
Someone even came to greet you
at the airport with a garland.

237
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:46,387
Hey, I told you
I just broke up with my boyfriend.

238
00:12:46,406 --> 00:12:47,963
I'm not ready to start over with anyone.

239
00:12:47,987 --> 00:12:49,470
I'm not telling you to start over.

240
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:51,446
I'm just letting you know.

241
00:12:51,476 --> 00:12:54,012
You don't have to accept his feelings now,

242
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:55,390
but just give him a chance.

243
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:57,040
Can't you see he's trying?

244
00:12:57,070 --> 00:12:57,876
Yeah.

245
00:12:57,901 --> 00:12:58,855
Listen to your friend.

246
00:12:58,898 --> 00:12:59,975
Right.

247
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:02,221
Fine, do whatever you want.

248
00:13:02,258 --> 00:13:02,836
Oh?

249
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:03,880
Oh?

250
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:04,713
Kanit!

251
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:05,476
Where are you going?

252
00:13:05,510 --> 00:13:06,455
We're going out tonight.

253
00:13:06,486 --> 00:13:07,486
Don't forget that!

254
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:11,107
You've got guts.

255
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:12,400
Thumbs up.

256
00:13:12,710 --> 00:13:15,113
Kanit is a little hard to please.

257
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:19,144
You might have to keep chasing him or
make things clear, but I'm rooting for you.

258
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:20,449
Keep fighting.

259
00:13:20,486 --> 00:13:22,283
I'll send you the location.

260
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:24,610
Well done.

261
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,264
Kanit, wait!

262
00:13:26,930 --> 00:13:27,930
Kanit!

263
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:29,212
I like you now!

264
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:30,664
You can't run away from me!

265
00:13:48,650 --> 00:13:49,650
Come on.

266
00:13:50,170 --> 00:13:50,572
Yeah.

267
00:13:50,603 --> 00:13:51,901
Cheers!

268
00:13:51,932 --> 00:13:54,436
You just became single,
so go all out tonight!

269
00:13:54,467 --> 00:13:55,822
I've been in a relationship for so long.

270
00:13:55,846 --> 00:13:59,796
Tonight, the world will know I'm single!

271
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,316
The whole bar knows it now.

272
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:04,980
Go!

273
00:14:05,187 --> 00:14:06,187
Cheers?

274
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:08,180
Of course.

275
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:11,729
Let me be honest. Can I hit on you?

276
00:14:12,030 --> 00:14:13,372
Yes, you can.

277
00:14:13,403 --> 00:14:15,046
My friend just became single.

278
00:14:15,064 --> 00:14:16,849
He wants to meet new people,

279
